===Etymology===

Hebrew ''šibbōlet'', ear of wheat.

===Noun===

'''shibboleth'''

#A word which was made the criterion by which to distinguish the Ephraimites from the Gileadites. The Ephraimites, not being able to pronounce ''sh'', called the word ''sibboleth''. See Judges xii.
#Also in an extended sense: the [[criterion]], [[test]], [[watchword]], or [[password]] of a party used to distinguish membership.
#A [[slogan]], [[jargon]] word, or [[catchphrase]] closely associated with a particular group and not used very much, or at all, outside of it. Can also apply to ideas, [[customs]], and uses of language.
#A common belief or usage that is questionable or incorrect; [[truism]], [[platitude]].

